title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1977-12-30
lineage: Master reel > Technics 1506 w/Lamb Labs Dolby decoder > Apogee Mini Me > wav 24/96 - transferred by Matt Smith; Lineage: Wav > Adobe Audition 1.5 > iZotope RX6 Advanced >iZotope Ozone 5 Advanced > CD Wave > TLH > Flac 24; edited and mastered SIRMick October 2017 - surround mixing by Kevin Tobin
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step, Me & My Uncle, Dire Wolf, Looks Like Rain, Row Jimmy, Big River, Peggy-O, Passenger, Ramble On Rose, Let It Grow

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Saint Stephen-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues, E: Good Lovin'

*Second Encore

reviews.review_text: What can I say? Great show has a great matrix.  Some folks don't like these, but personally I love having the clarity of the SBD with the gut-punch of the AUD, especially when it's done so well as it is here.  Many thanks for yet another great mix, your work is appreciated.
